The number of declared Covid-19 cases in Kenya has risen to 103,841 as 226 more people were found infected after the analysis of 4,606 samples in the past 24 hours. 

Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe made the announcement in a statement on Monday, saying 165 of them were Kenyans and 61 foreigners. 

CS Kagwe said 132 were male and 94 females, the youngest two years old and the oldest 98. 



